# Python FastAPI Backend Implementation Plan

## Goal Description
Build a Python backend using FastAPI to support the Agentic RAG Creation UI. The backend will handle processing data sources (scraping websites, reading uploaded documents), use a local LLM to converse with the user and determine the RAG configuration (e.g., Pinecone, ChromaDB), and finally create and deploy the customized RAG system.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Project Setup
#### [NEW] `backend/requirements.txt`(file:///c:/Users/e629/Documents/AgenticRag/backend/requirements.txt)
- `fastapi`, `uvicorn`, `pydantic`, `python-multipart`
- `langchain`, `langchain-community`, `beautifulsoup4` (for scraping)
- `pdfplumber` or `PyPDF2` (for document reading)
- `pinecone-client`, `chromadb` (Vector DBs)

#### [NEW] `backend/main.py`(file:///c:/Users/e629/Documents/AgenticRag/backend/main.py)
- Set up FastAPI app with CORS middleware.
- Implement endpoints:
  - `POST /api/scrape`: Accepts URLs, uses BeautifulSoup/Langchain loaders to extract text, and splits into chunks.
  - `POST /api/upload`: Accepts file uploads (PDF, TXT, DOCX), extracts text, and prepares it for embeddings.
  - `POST /api/chat`: Interacts with a local LLM to guide the user in selecting RAG features (Vector DB, Persona, Architecture) and answer questions about RAG types.
  - `POST /api/deploy`: Takes the parsed documents/URLs and chosen configuration, embeds the data, stores it in the selected Vector DB (Pinecone, ChromaDB), and returns the final RAG endpoint details.

